scene.message:
{wait_fr:32}I bet this guy's{wait_fr:32}{nl}
seein' the same thing{nl}
right now.{wait_fr:96}{ret}

Ms. Natsumi: You're awake,{nl}
{ctl0f:1}.{waitkey}{nl}
Hehe, welcome to the{nl}
nurse's office~{nl}
You looked so cute sleeping!{waitkey}{ret}

{color:3}Yoshino Natsumi.{nl}
St. Hermelin's school nurse.{nl}
Apparently not the best{nl}
cook in the world.{color:0}{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Saeko: Oh, thank goodness{nl}
you're awake, {ctl0f:1}!{waitkey}{clearbox}You scared me half to death{nl}
when I heard you'd collapsed!{waitkey}{ret}

{color:3}Takami Saeko.{nl}
Homeroom teacher for{nl}
{ctl0f:1}'s class.{nl}
Bright and well-loved.{color:0}{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Saeko: I'm so sorry,{nl}
Ms. Natsumi — my kids{nl}
caused you trouble!{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: That's literally your{nl}
job, lookin' after students.{nl}
Quit whinin'...{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Saeko: Inaba! Show some{nl}
remorse! {wait_fr:48}...Anyway, I{nl}
heard the gist from Kirishima{nl}
and Ayase, so...{waitkey}{clearbox}I'm canceling your{nl}
volunteer duty for today.{wait_fr:32}{nl}
Instead, swing by Mikage{nl}
General for a checkup!{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: So even the teacher{nl}
thinks something's wrong{nl}
with us?{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Saeko: Anyone with eyes{nl}
can see you're all fine.{waitkey}{clearbox}...But if you hit your head{nl}
when you fell, I need to{nl}
know you're checked out.{nl}
I'd just worry otherwise.{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: Didn't know you{nl}
worried about us, Ms. Saeko.{wait_fr:48}{nl}
Fine. We'll go.{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Natsumi: Oh, speaking of{nl}
Mikage General — don't you{nl}
have a student hospitalized{nl}
there, Ms. Saeko?{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Saeko: That's right.{nl}
So while you're there,{nl}
it's not out of the way —{nl}
go visit Sonemura.{waitkey}{clearbox}She's been there{nl}
almost a year now.{nl}
I'm sure she'd love{nl}
to see some familiar faces.{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Saeko: I asked you to{nl}
help prep for the Festival.{nl}
How did you end up{nl}
collapsed in an empty room?{waitkey}{clearbox}The Festival is barely{nl}
a month away and nothing's{nl}
been arranged yet. Should I{nl}
just cancel it this year?{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: That would be{nl}
most practical.{nl}
Best to dispose of{nl}
such nuisances swiftly.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Mikage Hospital, right?{nl}
Pretty long walk from school{nl}
— it's northeast of here.{waitkey}{clearbox}Head out of school, go right,{nl}
then turn right at the main{nl}
street...{wait_fr:21}and left at the{nl}
end of the road!{waitkey}{clearbox}Uh,{wait_fr:32} just wander around{nl}
and you'll get there.{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: Being in a hospital{nl}
for a whole year... no way{nl}
I could take that.{wait_fr:32}{nl}
Let's all cheer her up!{waitkey}{ret}

Ms. Saeko: Hey!{wait_fr:32}{nl}
Get over to Mikage General{nl}
Hospital now!{waitkey}{ret}

Agastya Tree: Young one...{nl}
You have come before me.{nl}
Welcome.{waitkey}{ret}

Agastya Tree:{nl}
Shall I inscribe your{nl}
record within me?{waitkey}{nl}
{ctl0e:0}{ret}

Ms. Natsumi: I put a new{nl}
houseplant in here. Nice,{nl}
isn't it?{waitkey}{clearbox}They say plants grow better{nl}
if you talk to them.{waitkey}{clearbox}{ctl0f:1},{nl}
why don't you say hello{nl}
to it sometime?{waitkey}{ret}
